OL,3,CEl Nino returns, raising fears of more
OL,4,Cextreme weather and higher food prices
OL,6,FEl Nino develops every few years in
OL,7,Fthe Pacific Ocean. Under normal
OL,8,Fconditions, strong trade winds push
OL,9,Fwarm surface waters towards Asia. But
OL,10,Fduring an El Nino event, those winds
OL,11,Fweaken, allowing warm water to spread
OL,12,Fback towards South America.
OL,14,FThat releases more heat into the
OL,15,Fatmosphere, disrupting weather
OL,16,Fpatterns around the world.
OL,26,@kD@FTwnD@FTwrD@PTw
