OL,3,CEl Nino returns, raising fears of more
OL,4,Cextreme weather and higher food prices
OL,6,FRegions that typically become drier
OL,7,Fduring El Nino events often face an
OL,8,Fincreased risk of drought and
OL,9,Fwildfire. Other parts of the world
OL,10,Ftend to experience heavier rainfall.
OL,12,FIn Kenya, severe flooding killed
OL,13,Fhundreds of people, washed away crops
OL,14,Fand left around half a million people
OL,15,Fhomeless.
OL,17,FThe UK is less directly affected by El
OL,18,FNino, but scientists say it can still
OL,19,Finfluence weather patterns. During the
OL,20,Flast event, Britain recorded its
OL,21,Fhottest spring on record in 2024.
OL,26,@kD@FTwoD@MTwzD@CTw
