OL,3,CEl Nino returns, raising fears of more
OL,4,Cextreme weather and higher food prices
OL,6,FGareth Redmond-King, International
OL,7,FLead at the Energy and Climate
OL,8,FIntelligence Unit, said: "We import
OL,9,Faround two-fifths of our food. Things
OL,10,Fthat we can't grow in the UK, like
OL,11,Fbananas, rice and coffee. El Nino is
OL,12,Fgoing to put a rocket under those
OL,13,Fclimate change impacts and turbocharge
OL,14,Fthose price rises, which go up very
OL,15,Ffast but take much longer to come
OL,16,Fdown."
OL,18,FScientists stress that while El Nino
OL,19,Fis a natural climate cycle, it is
OL,20,Funfolding against a backdrop of long-
OL,21,Fterm global warming.
OL,26,@kD@FTwsD@`TwzD@cTw
